The paper proposes classification algorithms that leverage supervision from coarser resolutions to help train models on finer resolutions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions real-world applications of mapping urban areas using satellite observations and sentiment classification on text data, which suggests that it could also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
